value.value: any anomaly in the process whereby the implantation chamber orients in the uterus in response to decidual growth to insure correct alignment of the embryo to the uterus
an anomaly in the degree to which (for each species) the uterine epithelium closes over and makes contact with, and secures an implanting blastocyst
any anomaly that prevents the initial positioning of the blastocyst trophoblast and uterine luminal epithelium causing the blastocyst to fail to orientate correctly along the uterine wall
any anomaly in the process whereby the blastocyst anchors to the uterine luminal epithelium and cannot be dislodged by flushing
any anomaly in the process that enables the embryo to establish connection to the uterine luminal epithelium
a fertilized egg attaches and begins development in a location other than in the inner lining of the uterus, most commonly in the Fallopian tube
failure of the uterus to undergo the changes necessary to support pregnancy following implantation of the embryo
any anomaly in vascular permeability and blood vessel development that normally occurs in the uterus to support embryonic growth during pregnancy
any functional anomaly of the female muscular organ of gestation in which the developing embryo or fetus is nourished until birth
anomaly in average weight at birth compared to controls
increase in average weight at birth compared to controls
reduction in average weight at birth compared to controls
thickening of the stratum corneum of the epidermis (hyperkeratosis) with non-nucleated keratinocytes retained in this layer
any anomaly in the spontaneous arrest of bleeding from vessels carrying blood under pressure or the arrest of circulation to an organ or part

label.value: abnormal spinal cord dorsal column morphology

value.value: any structural anomaly of the wedge-shaped fiber bundle of white matter in the dorsomedial side of the spinal cord that is made up of the fasciculus gracilis and fasciculus cuneatus; it is part of the ascending posterior column-medial lemniscus pathway that is important for well-localized fine touch and conscious proprioception

definition.value: Note that the synonym posterior column may refer to either the grey matter dorsal horn or the white matter dorsal column in the spinal cord.

label.value: abnormal spinal cord lateral column morphology

value.value: any structural anomaly of the region of white matter of the spinal cord that is located between the dorsal and ventral spinal roots

label.value: abnormal spinal cord ventral column morphology

value.value: any structural anomaly of the area of white matter of the spinal cord located on either side of the ventral (anterior) medial fissure

definition.value: Note that the synonym anterior column may refer to either the grey matter ventral horn or the white matter ventral column in the spinal cord.

label.value: abnormal medulla oblongata anterior median fissure morphology

value.value: any structural anomaly of the longitudinal groove in the midline of the anterior aspect of the medulla oblongata
any structural anomaly of the bundles of pyramidal fibers that intercross obliquely over the midline at the lower border region of the medulla oblongata

any structural anomaly of the small bundle of corticospinal motor fibers that do not cross the midline at the pyramidal decussation and descend into the anterior funiculus of the spinal cord; the anterior corticospinal tract controls central axial and girdle muscles

any structural anomaly of the large bundle of corticospinal motor fibers that cross the midline at the pyramidal decussation and descend in the dorsal half of the lateral funiculus; the lateral corticospinal tract controls movement of contralateral limbs

label.value: abnormal spinal cord lateral motor column morphology

value.value: any structural anomaly of the subclasses of motor neurons which innervate muscles in the limb; motor neurons in the lateral motor column are further organized into pools, each of which innervates a specific muscle in the limb

label.value: abnormal spinal cord motor column morphology

value.value: any structural anomaly of the subclasses of motor neurons which are organized into longitudinally oriented columns that occupy distinct and, in some cases, discontinuous domains along the rostrocaudal axis of the spinal cord; motor neurons within a single column send their axons to a common peripheral target

label.value: abnormal spinal cord medial motor column morphology

value.value: any structural anomaly of the subclasses of motor neurons which project their axons to axial muscles that lie close to the vertebral column; motor neurons in the lateral subdivision of the MMC project their axons to body wall muscles

the implanted embryo normally covered opposite the placenta by uterine mucosa and epithelium following implantation is missing, suggesting the embryo died early during implantation but after the decidual response and modification of uterine stromal cells

label.value: abnormal spinal cord central canal morphology

value.value: any structural anomaly of the ependyma-lined lumen of the spinal cord that is filled with cerebrospinal fluid; it is patent with the ventricular system of the brain and frequently becomes occluded in aging adults

label.value: abnormal neural tube ventricular layer morphology

value.value: any structural anomaly of the layer of undifferentiated, proliferating cells that line the neural tube lumen

label.value: abnormal neural tube mantle layer morphology

value.value: any structural anomaly of the layer of glia and differentiating neurons that will form the gray matter of the spinal cord; this lies between the ventricular and marginal layers and includes the basal and alar plates

label.value: abnormal neural tube marginal layer morphology

value.value: any structural anomaly of the outermost layer of the neural tube that contains nerve fibers and will form the white matter

label.value: abnormal spinal cord alar plate morphology

value.value: any structural anomaly of the region of the mantle layer of the neural tube that lies dorsal to the sulcus limitans and contains primarily sensory neurons and interneurons involved in communication of sensory impulses; the alar plate develops into the dorsal horn in the grey matter of the spinal cord

label.value: abnormal spinal cord basal plate morphology

value.value: any structural anomaly of the region of the mantle layer of the neural tube that lies ventral to the sulcus limitans and contains primarily motor neurons and interneurons
any structural anomaly of any of the nerve fiber tracts that span the midline of the spinal cord

label.value: abnormal spinal cord ventral commissure morphology

value.value: any structural anomaly of the band of nerve fibers which cross the midline of the spinal cord ventral to the central canal and posterior grey commissure

label.value: abnormal spinal cord grey commissure morphology

value.value: any structural anomaly of the band of grey substance spanning the midline of the spinal cord that surrounds the central canal
an anomaly in sexual union that normally enables the transfer of ejaculate (sperm) from male to female, sometimes resulting in the fertilization of an egg
bleeding into the heart

increased plasma concentrations of chylomicrons, the large lipid droplet (up to 100 mm in diameter) of reprocessed lipid synthesized in epithelial cells of the small intestine and containing triacylglycerols, cholesterol esters, and several apolipoproteins
anomaly in average body size at birth compared to controls
increase in average body size at birth compared to controls
reduction in average body size at birth compared to controls

label.value: increased skin squamous cell carcinoma incidence

value.value: greater than the expected number of a skin carcinoma derived from stratified squamous epithelium, occurring in a specific population in a given time period
any structural anomaly of the portion of the embryonic gut between the foregut and the hindgut, which originally is open to the yolk sac
absence of the portion of the embryonic gut between the foregut and the hindgut
absence of the canal that connects the outer and middle ear

a longitudinal or transverse congenital partition within the muscular canal extending from outside of the body to the cervix; usually caused by incomplete fusion of the Mullerian ducts in embryogenesis
an accumulation in the uterine lumen of normal secretions that ordinarily drain from the body but are retained when the cervix or vagina is significantly or completely closed
inability to experience pleasure in response to normally pleasurable stimuli
anomaly in the ability of an animal to learn and remember an association between a putative rewarding internal state produced by a xenobiotic or drug with a neutral, unchanging environment
decrease in the ability of an animal to learn and remember an association between a putative rewarding internal state produced by a xenobiotic or drug with a neutral, unchanging environment
